			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Frustrating!<a name="55627"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 8 04 10:14 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I have tried autocircling and find it more frustrating than your problem so the best thing to do is two things.  First you should determine if the song you are playing has a kickback or knockback effect.  I twist DDD in Iceclad without Selos and I just stay ahead of the cougars, when I see the song hit I notice they get kicked just out of range.  (only just)  But, still they do tend to hit you.  What you want is a run3 aa effect which is slower than Sow/Soe and definately slower than Selo but faster than run3.  The solution to you problem is journeyman boots.  They offer a clickable 18 minute instant cast run enhancement that is just fast enough to stay ahead of most of the non accelerated mobs.  The quest for jboots is really simple and takes only a day.  Just a note if you decide to do the jboots quest dont bother with hunting the AC (ancient cyclops) in So Ro do the one in Ocean of Tears he has a set spawn point and if you get to camp it you are guaranteed to get one of the two pieces fairly easily.  you dont have to wear the boots just have them in an open slot and create a shortcut in your hotbuttons to it.  Before a kite you hit it, then twist your favorite dots.  check your time left and in between mobs recast it.  I kited iceclad cougars, wolves, and even midnight (black cougar which is faster than the others) no problems.  That was up to level 42 without ever using selo's.  Then I went to Timorous Deep and kited the Spriocs till level 50.  (all the spirocs about 20 to 25 of em) getting about 2 yellows per kite at 43 to about 1 yellow per kite at 50.  The other more important thing is practice practice practice.  Go to a zone with some greens kite them and play with your camera views.  I myself prefer 3rd person view for kiting and I stay away from auto circle cause for the most part mobs will cut to the center and have the chance to whack you from there and it only takes one hit to stun or one bash to stop your song and I have heard of stories of peeps going to get a coke thinking they had things locked in and when the came back ... dead.  worse case do figure 8's or a barbell shaped path.  You will find your sweet spot no matter.  Second, kiting is the greatest way to gain huge leaps in levels and pp, but it also has a nasty side effect of gimping a bards defensive skill level.  You need to get hit to raise this and if you only kite all the way through your levels you will find yourself hurting later on at 50+.  Do as many ldons as you can in between every two or so levels to keep you defense up to date so to speak.  Hope this helps.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
